    "recap_headline": "Murray State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "MURFREESBORO, Tenn. \u2013\nLed by a five-run fourth inning and a staff effort from eight pitchers, the Racers defeated Middle Tennessee on Tuesday, avenging a previous midweek loss to the Blue Raiders.\nAll runs for Murray State (13-8) came in the fourth inning, sparked by three consecutive singles from\nConnor Chisolm\n,\nLuke Mistone\n, and\nKristofer Hokenson\n. Hokenson's hit put the Racers' first run on the board.\nAnthony Perritano\ndrove in two more with a single up the middle, scoring Hokenson and\nKainen Jorge\n.\nColby Ott\ncapped the rally with a double down the left-field line to drive in two more. Ott's double was the only extra-base hit of the day for Murray State.\n\"Well, the wind was blowing in,\" head coach\nDan Skirka\nsaid, \"and as a hitter you know that. So we knew we had to stay on the barrel and stay on a line and string some hits together; we weren't going to hit the ball out of the ballpark. So, I was proud of them for that, and we executed two bunt hits, which is huge.\"\nThe Racers used eight arms throughout the afternoon, with\nDylan Zentko\nmaking his first start of the year. Zentko set the tone with a scoreless first inning, while Hokenson and\nParker Patterson\ncompleted the first four innings to keep Middle Tennessee (12-9) off the board.\nEthan Lyke\n,\nJack Wajda\n, and\nJackson Ugo\neach made appearances on the mound, allowing one run apiece.\nLogan Smothers\nearned his second win of the 2026 campaign, tossing 1.1 innings of scoreless relief and striking out two.\n\"We got the leadoff guy out eight out of nine times,\" Skirka said. \"So it's tough to rally for an offense when they don't get that leadoff guy on base. We minimized the freebies; we only had four walks. So, for eight guys to go out there and piece together a three-run game, it's phenomenal.\"\nMurray State looks to carry the momentum into the weekend as Missouri Valley Conference play begins with a series against Valparaiso in Evansville.\nBox Score Notes\nKristofer Hokenson\nextended his team-leading reached base streak to 14 \u2026\nAnthony Perritano\nrecorded his third multi-hit game and his third multi-RBI game of the season \u2026 Just the second road win at MTSU since 1996 \u2026 Most Pitchers used in a game this season \u2026 Racers move to 3-2 in midweek matchups"
  },
